{"title": "Three Acres and Liberty", "description": "It (this book) shows what is needed for a city man or woman to support a family on the proceeds of a little bit of land; it shows how in truth, as the old Book prophesied, the earth brings forth abundantly after its kind to satisfy the desire of every living thing. It is not necessary to bury oneself in the country, nor, with the new facilities of transportation, need we, unless we wish to, pay the extravagant rents and enormous cost of living in the city. A little bit of land near the town or the city can be rented or bought on easy terms; and merchandising will bring one to the city often enough. Neither is hard labor needed; but it is to work alone that the earth yields her increase, and if, although unskilled, we would succeed in gardening, we must attend constantly and intelligently to the home acres. - Summary by Bolton Hall", "duration": 33320, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "14248", "name": "Bolton Hall"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/threeacresandliberty_2511_librivox/threeacresandliberty_2511.jpg", "copyright_year": "1918", "genres": ["Gardening"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Amy Gramour"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Amy Gramour"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Amy Gramour"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Forward", "readers": [10244], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/threeacresandliberty_2511_librivox/threeacres_00_hall_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1405}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I: Making a Living\u2014Where and How", "readers": [10159], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/threeacresandliberty_2511_librivox/threeacres_01_hall_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1201}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter II: Present Conditions", "readers": [10159], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/threeacresandliberty_2511_librivox/threeacres_02_hall_64kb.mp3", "duration": 729}, {"sect